# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your Discord webhook URL.
# .env.local is git-ignored by default (Vite convention) so the URL stays local.
#
# To create a webhook:
#   Discord → Server Settings → Integrations → Webhooks → New Webhook
#   Copy the Webhook URL and paste it below.
#
# After editing .env.local, restart the dev server so Vite picks it up.
#
# NOTE: Anything prefixed with VITE_ is bundled into client-side JS, meaning
# the URL is visible to anyone visiting the site. For a low-traffic wedding
# site that's normally fine, but be aware that a determined visitor could
# spam your channel. If that becomes an issue, move the call behind a
# server-side proxy.

VITE_DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL=
